Key Match Events: Rhett Lowder pitched 5 1/3 innings, giving up three earned runs and six hits with one walk and five strikeouts.
The Twins scored three runs in the bottom of the sixth inning, leading to a 9-2 victory over the Reds.
Ryan Jeffers hit a game-tying RBI double in the sixth inning.
Brooks Lee added a two-run single in the sixth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Twins manager Rocco Baldelli expressed his impression with Rhett Lowder's performance.
Reds manager David Bell praised Lowder's ability to compete and give the team a chance to win.
Rhett Lowder reflected on his performance and the experience gained from facing strong teams.
